      <title>Companion Seals why were they removed?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&amp;message.id=10480#M10480</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;I noticed that pet augments were removed from the game.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; The question I have is why?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; Pet classes are typically at disadvantage in the game to get pet augs. These items are hard to quest after but are rewarding for those looking to augment their pets. The fact remains by placing an item that's avaiable in  popular raids it allows the pet classes a shot at getting pet augs they desperately need to stay on par with other classes.Instead the augments were suspended and SOE has been very very vague about why, however, Sony sees nothing wrong with straight classes using the augments to increase their dps all out. For those new to the subject here is a list of  the seals that have been disabled:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Bazu Seal of companions&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Chronal Seal of companions&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Discordant Seal of companions&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;To my knowledge all other seals for the melee and other classes remain intact. Please correct me if this is wrong.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Currently the only way to get some the higher end pet augmentations in this game is by similar methods in COA or higher raids. Even the boot drop in COA which gives nearly the same effect is sought after by other classes for what it does for them. By opening up a few more avenues for pet classes you give them better chance to increase their pets dps and make them valued for it on raids and soloing.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;From your recent actions taken against pets it is my opinion that you unjustly favor classes that dont really rely on pets for DPS. This means any new players should seriously consider not playing mages or beasts. The pet focus and hold commands did much to restore pets to raids, but by limiting pet progression (with augs) pets are still not considered of any value to raids no matter how skilled their owners are with them. I am not asking for pets dps to match a tank they are after all supplement to dps not the where with all.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Please explain how disabling the above augs harmed classes that already brag about out dpsing mages, and beastlords. Both  these classes were once on par with other classes for dps and abilites but seem with each expansion to fall lower and lower on the dps ladder.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Please explain how these aug gave mages, beastlords, or even necro pets a unfair advantage over other players which requried their removal from the game.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
