e years the minute a tank tradeskill is messed up it gets patched fast. I know the coders are overworked that issue isnt in doubt, however, someone should got the augments right the first time they came out. Not say ok the first few people to get this item grats, but  the rest of  the people can wait 3 years for the code patch  to upgrade and again be behind the power curve in the game.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; So why aren't  the augments being fixed ? &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Please do not respond with a comment about how it unfairly gives SK, Shammy, and druid pets an unfair advantage the harm done to the main pet classes far outweigh any such argument. I know something about computers and if thats the case it wouldnt take much coding to alters the new augments to be mage, necro, and beastlord only equippable and keep the handful augs out there as all/all a rare and special find to the few who discovered it before patching.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Sony has had many many months to patch this item but clearly they dont seem to be in any way working towards a fair solution.I realize that you have limited manpower and that you have to deal with bigger priorties first, but dont put something off to the side forever that was caused by coding error and not the players fault.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
